International flights to and from Côte d’Ivoire have been suspended until further notice, except for humanitarian and security purposes. Land borders are also closed.
There are currently no commercial options available to return to the UK from Côte d’Ivoire.
We know this is concerning for British people trying to leave Côte d’Ivoire.
If you cannot leave Côte d’Ivoire at this time, see advice on staying in Côte d’Ivoire during coronavirus.
Future options
This travel advice will be updated when departure options become available.
You will need to pay for your return travel to the UK. If departure options are available but you cannot afford the travel costs and have exhausted all other options for getting funds, you may be eligible to apply for an emergency loan from the government. This is a last resort option and you would need to repay the loan when you are back in the UK. For more information, you should contact Corporate Travel Management (CTM). CTM are a commercial partner of the FCO and are authorised to administer such loans on behalf of the FCO.
Your journey home
The National Travel Health Network and Centre (NaTHNaC) provides advice on how to stay safe as you travel by air.
If you’re returning home before 8 June, follow the guidance for when you return to the UK on steps you should take to protect yourself and others. From 8 June there will be new rules for entering the UK.
Help and support
If you need urgent consular assistance, you can contact the British Embassy Abidjan by phone on +225 22442669 or by email to British.Embassy.Abidjan@fco.gov.uk
The Embassy cannot provide further information or advice about departure options over the phone. This page will be updated when departure options become available.
To get the latest information, sign up for travel advice email alerts and follow the British Embassy Abidjan on Twitter and Facebook
Further information
See additional advice on making travel plans to return to the UK, or what to do if you cannot depart immediately.
